Docker is used to containerize applications so they can run consistently across different environments.
containerization = application code + dependencies
Architectures:
Monolithic Architecture:Entire application built as one single unit.
Microservices Architecture: Application split into small independent services.
A Docker image is a read-only template that contains everything needed to run an application and is used to create containers.
Container - A container is a lightweight virtualization technology that packages an application with its dependencies and runs using the host OS kernel.
Launch an ec2 > install docker(yum install docker -y) > docker version > systemctl start docker.
Docker consists of the Docker Client, Docker Daemon, Images, Containers, Registry, and Docker Engine.
Docker file is used to create images.






